# Navigation

Navigators live in `src/navigators/`. The root stack is `Application.tsx`; route param types live in `src/types/navigation.d.ts`.

## Typed routes

Every `Stack.Screen` `name` must exist on `ApplicationStackParamList`. Screens with no params use `undefined`; screens with params define an object type.

```typescript
// src/types/navigation.d.ts
export type ApplicationStackParamList = {
  Home: undefined;
  SignIn: undefined;
  Profile: { userId: string };
};
```

Import the param list in navigators: `createStackNavigator<ApplicationStackParamList>()`.

## Registering a screen

When adding a route, update **both** files:

1. `ApplicationStackParamList` in `src/types/navigation.d.ts`
2. `<Stack.Screen name="..." component={...} />` in the navigator

Import screen components from `@/screens`, not from deep paths.

## Auth gating

The root navigator switches stacks based on `useUserStore(state => state.isLoggedIn)`. Keep auth screens in the logged-out group and app screens in the logged-in group:

```typescript
{isLoggedIn ? (
  <Stack.Group>
    <Stack.Screen name="Home" component={Home} />
  </Stack.Group>
) : (
  <Stack.Group>
    <Stack.Screen name="SignIn" component={SignIn} />
  </Stack.Group>
)}
```

Do not put auth logic inside individual screens — gate at the navigator level.

## Extending navigation

- **New authenticated screen** — add to the logged-in `Stack.Group`.
- **New auth screen** — add to the logged-out `Stack.Group`.
- **Tabs** — nest a tab navigator as a single stack screen inside the logged-in group; do not replace the root `NavigationContainer`.
- **Modal flows** — use a nested stack or `presentation: 'modal'` on a group; keep `ApplicationStackParamList` as the single source of route names.
